WEBVTT

00:00.200 --> 00:02.700
[Julie] Your Honor,
this is a medical support dog.

00:02.767 --> 00:06.967
[Judge Judy] So, he damaged the gate
which you have to have fixed?

00:07.433 --> 00:09.100
Yes.

00:09.166 --> 00:12.500
He made sixteen cuts,
eight in the front.

00:12.567 --> 00:14.600
- Not true.
- Oh, my God.

00:14.667 --> 00:18.400
You don't look like you need
an emotional support dog for anything.

00:18.467 --> 00:20.633
[announcer]
<i>This is </i>Judy Justice.

00:20.700 --> 00:22.066
[♪ theme music playing]

00:37.467 --> 00:40.533
[announcer] <i>Julie Mondin</i>
<i>is suing welder Martin Lucas</i>

00:40.600 --> 00:42.934
<i>for gate damage and repair costs.</i>

00:45.066 --> 00:47.033
[Kevin]
All rise. Court come to order.

00:49.367 --> 00:50.867
Be seated, please.

00:53.367 --> 00:56.266
Hello, Judge.
Case 1044, Mondin vs. Lucas.

00:56.333 --> 00:57.333
Thank you.

00:57.400 --> 00:59.667
Ms. Mondin, I've read your papers,

00:59.734 --> 01:03.367
and I don't see anything in your papers
involving the dog,

01:03.433 --> 01:04.967
so can you tell me why the dog is here?

01:05.033 --> 01:08.400
Your Honor, this is a medical support dog.

01:08.467 --> 01:12.033
Um, sometimes when I don't eat enough
sodium or glucose,

01:12.100 --> 01:16.200
then I faint or, you know,
have a medical emergency.

01:16.266 --> 01:21.133
So, she's trained to detect blood sugar
and blood pressure.

01:21.200 --> 01:26.300
Okay. This is the case which
doesn't appear to be too difficult.

01:26.767 --> 01:31.500
You hired the defendant
to do some iron work at your home.

01:31.567 --> 01:35.967
You wanted some decorative work done
on your iron gate.

01:36.033 --> 01:38.767
From what I read in your papers,

01:38.834 --> 01:41.500
the defendant had done work for you
previously,

01:41.567 --> 01:44.967
which you were satisfied with
and paid him for.

01:46.367 --> 01:48.300
- If I may, Your Honor.
- It's either a yes or a no.

01:48.367 --> 01:50.100
Had he done work for you previously?

01:50.166 --> 01:51.734
Only on the gate, so yes.

01:51.800 --> 01:56.100
So the answer is he had done work for you
previously that you were satisfied with?

01:56.166 --> 01:57.600
- [Julie] Yes.
- And you paid him?

01:57.767 --> 02:01.000
- Yes.
- And then for this particular job,

02:01.066 --> 02:03.633
you wanted to add some decorative stuff.

02:03.700 --> 02:08.000
And first give me a timeframe,
month and year.

02:08.066 --> 02:10.133
Beginning of October,
October 9th, 2020.

02:11.266 --> 02:14.367
[Judge Judy] Did you call him
or did you text him about this job?

02:14.433 --> 02:15.734
How did you reach out to him?

02:15.800 --> 02:18.033
I found him on Craigslist
as a welder. I texted him--

02:18.100 --> 02:19.100
[Judge Judy] Well, that was--

02:21.734 --> 02:24.400
he had done work for you before,

02:24.467 --> 02:26.066
so you must have had his number.

02:27.033 --> 02:31.333
No. He did work for me
before the day we had this kerfuffle,

02:31.400 --> 02:32.867
but he only did work on the gate.

02:32.934 --> 02:34.133
The gate was a project.

02:34.200 --> 02:35.367
Ms. Mondin...

02:36.667 --> 02:38.734
when did he first go to your house?

02:38.800 --> 02:42.600
What month and year,
to work on the gate?

02:42.667 --> 02:44.300
September, 2020.

02:44.367 --> 02:47.033
Okay. And he did work on the gate...

02:47.100 --> 02:48.600
- [Julie] Yes.
- ...in September.

02:48.667 --> 02:51.066
And what did he charge you in September?

02:51.133 --> 02:53.367
Between $400 a day on one day,

02:53.433 --> 02:55.333
$450 a day on another day.

02:56.233 --> 02:59.066
So he came on two separate occasions

02:59.133 --> 03:03.233
between September and October 9th?

03:03.300 --> 03:08.934
On two separate occasions,
one $400 and the other one for 450?

03:09.000 --> 03:10.800
And a third time also.

03:10.867 --> 03:12.266
- And he came a third time?
- Yes.

03:12.333 --> 03:13.533
And how much was that?

03:13.600 --> 03:16.200
I would have to look, I think it was $420.

03:16.266 --> 03:19.600
Okay. And he did work
on the gate and you paid him?

03:19.667 --> 03:23.233
- Yes.
- And did you pay him by check or cash?

03:23.300 --> 03:27.233
Check one time,
and then he requested cash only,

03:27.300 --> 03:28.700
cash the rest of the times.

03:28.767 --> 03:33.800
So, the last two times
he worked for you, he requested cash?

03:33.867 --> 03:36.033
- Yes.
- Then on October 9th,

03:36.100 --> 03:40.533
you reached out to him again
to do additional work.

03:40.600 --> 03:43.600
And my question was,
did you reach out to him again

03:43.667 --> 03:47.400
by phone or by text on October 9th?

03:47.467 --> 03:50.100
Or did you tell him on a previous day,

03:50.166 --> 03:52.367
"Come back, I want you to do more work?"

03:52.934 --> 03:55.300
Previous day, we were texting.

03:55.367 --> 03:57.367
Okay. Do you have a copy of the texts

03:57.433 --> 04:01.867
where you made an agreement
to pay him $500 to do that work?

04:02.533 --> 04:05.500
I have a receipt, Your Honor,
but I don't think I have that.

04:05.567 --> 04:08.567
He would always give me
a receipt the day of.

04:08.633 --> 04:13.800
Okay. But he had to have told you
what the cost was, that's a contract.

04:13.867 --> 04:16.834
Right. I have three previous invoices,

04:16.900 --> 04:19.800
and he would write the invoice
when he got there, not before.

04:19.867 --> 04:22.667
Okay. Did he write
an invoice on October 9th?

04:22.734 --> 04:23.800
He did not.

04:23.867 --> 04:27.100
Okay. Did he tell you
on October 9th what the cost would be?

04:27.166 --> 04:28.400
- Yes. And I--
- Wait just a second.

04:28.467 --> 04:29.467
Okay.

04:29.533 --> 04:31.567
And what did he tell you
the cost would be?

04:31.633 --> 04:33.133
$450.

04:33.200 --> 04:35.266
And on October 9th,

04:35.333 --> 04:39.333
did he complete the job
that he was supposed to?

04:39.400 --> 04:42.467
- Yes.
- And on October 9th,

04:42.533 --> 04:46.133
you had a conversation with him
after the job was completed,

04:46.200 --> 04:49.133
according to you and according to him,

04:49.200 --> 04:53.633
that you didn't have money
that day to pay him?

04:53.700 --> 04:55.333
- Yes.
- Okay.

04:55.400 --> 04:59.000
And you told him that
after he had finished the day's work?

04:59.066 --> 05:01.400
- No.
- When did you tell him that?

05:01.467 --> 05:02.633
Before he finished.

05:02.700 --> 05:04.133
I was just getting ready to pay him.

05:04.200 --> 05:06.467
It was around to 4:30, 4:15.

05:06.533 --> 05:08.834
Well, you were just getting
ready to pay him with what?

05:08.900 --> 05:10.166
Cash.

05:10.233 --> 05:11.433
Now, that's not what you said...

05:11.500 --> 05:12.500
- Well...
- ...Ms. Mondin.

05:12.567 --> 05:13.834
[Julie] I asked him if he had PayPal

05:13.900 --> 05:17.734
because I didn't have enough cash on hand.

05:17.800 --> 05:19.166
I never said I wasn't going to pay him.
I said I didn't have enough cash.

05:19.233 --> 05:21.100
No, no, I--no.

05:22.266 --> 05:24.867
You had previously paid him in cash.

05:24.934 --> 05:26.266
Yes.

05:26.333 --> 05:28.900
And on the 9th of October,

05:28.967 --> 05:32.066
you said, "Do you have PayPal?

05:32.133 --> 05:34.867
- I don't have cash." That's what...
- Right. Yes.

05:34.934 --> 05:35.934
- Okay.
- Yes.

05:36.000 --> 05:39.500
- And he said no, he doesn't have PayPal.
- Right.

05:39.567 --> 05:41.600
- Correct?
- Correct.

05:41.667 --> 05:42.667
- Okay.
- Not true, but...

05:42.734 --> 05:44.133
- Sure.
- Okay.

05:45.066 --> 05:47.166
Well, you know, I actually understand

05:47.233 --> 05:49.433
that you think that that
may be peculiar, Ms. Mondin.

05:49.500 --> 05:50.633
I don't have PayPal.

05:50.700 --> 05:51.800
I don't know what it is.

05:51.867 --> 05:53.233
I don't understand that whole thing.

05:53.300 --> 05:56.066
Money flies through the air,
through the airwaves,

05:56.133 --> 05:57.133
I don't understand it.

05:57.200 --> 06:01.000
I understand it when you go into a bank,
you fill out a withdrawal slip,

06:01.066 --> 06:03.934
you give it to a teller,
the teller gives you money,

06:04.000 --> 06:05.100
and you leave the bank.

06:05.166 --> 06:06.767
That--

06:06.834 --> 06:07.967
- I get it.
- That's what I understand.

06:08.033 --> 06:09.100
I get it.

06:09.166 --> 06:11.767
I also did other work
at her house as well, so...

06:11.834 --> 06:13.333
Not before the gate.

06:13.400 --> 06:14.400
- Just a second...
- [Martin] I haven't been to your house...

06:14.467 --> 06:16.533
You made--just shh.

06:17.200 --> 06:19.233
If you talk to each other,
you don't need me.

06:19.300 --> 06:21.600
- Okay.
- Then I won't have a job.

06:22.333 --> 06:23.767
Then they won't have a job.

06:29.133 --> 06:31.367
