I don't understand it.

06:53.400 --> 06:57.133
I understand it when you go into a bank,
you fill out a withdrawal slip,

06:57.200 --> 07:00.066
you give it to a teller,
the teller gives you money,

07:00.133 --> 07:03.066
and you leave the bank. That...

07:03.133 --> 07:04.700
- [Julie] I get it. I get it.
- That's what I understand.

07:04.767 --> 07:07.667
You know, I don't understand
putting your phone up next to something

07:07.734 --> 07:12.567
and people have been paid
or clicking an orange, the store,

07:12.633 --> 07:18.200
and somehow the merchant gets paid
for that orange and you just leave.

07:18.934 --> 07:21.033
One day I will figure it out,

07:21.100 --> 07:25.233
or one of my children or grandchildren
will try to explain it to me

07:25.300 --> 07:26.834
so I actually do understand it.

07:26.900 --> 07:28.867
- But he doesn't have PayPal.
- [Julie] No.

07:28.934 --> 07:30.600
- And he wanted to get paid.
- [Julie] Yes.

07:30.667 --> 07:32.934
So there was a kerfuffle.

07:33.000 --> 07:37.500
And during the kerfuffle,
Mr. Lucas acknowledges

07:37.567 --> 07:42.100
that he took off the work
that he did that day

07:42.166 --> 07:43.333
- and it is your--
- [Martin] Okay.

07:43.400 --> 07:45.266
Shh. Just a second. And it is your--

07:45.333 --> 07:49.266
it is your claim that in doing so,

07:49.333 --> 07:53.033
he damaged the fence or the gate?

07:53.100 --> 07:54.100
The gate.

07:54.166 --> 07:56.533
The gate,
which you have to have fixed.

07:56.600 --> 08:00.133
Mr. Lucas says that actually
what you said to him was,

08:00.200 --> 08:03.100
"I don't have money today,"

08:03.166 --> 08:06.266
and you had somewhat of a hissy fit

08:06.333 --> 08:08.266
because you expected to be paid.

08:08.333 --> 08:11.300
You couldn't find the keys to your truck,
according to you,

08:11.367 --> 08:14.233
and you sat around her house for a while.

08:14.300 --> 08:16.166
[Martin]
Waiting for the locksmith, yeah.

08:17.333 --> 08:18.800
- For your truck?
- [Martin] Yep.

08:18.867 --> 08:20.667
And according to you--

08:20.734 --> 08:22.166
Because it mysteriously disappeared.

08:22.233 --> 08:27.834
According to you,
Ms. Mondin left, came back,

08:27.900 --> 08:33.133
and she handed you $200 in cash

08:33.200 --> 08:35.467
- that she says she got from her sister.
- Friend.

08:35.533 --> 08:37.066
- A friend.
- Neighbor.

08:37.133 --> 08:40.233
And a $300 gift card.

08:41.100 --> 08:42.200
- Right?
- Yes, ma'am.

08:42.266 --> 08:44.433
And you accepted?

08:44.500 --> 08:45.867
- I did.
- But you--just a second.

08:45.934 --> 08:49.533
You accepted the $200 in cash

08:49.600 --> 08:52.800
and the $300 gift card.

08:52.867 --> 08:54.033
You accepted it.

08:54.667 --> 08:57.900
And furthermore, Mr. Lucas,

08:57.967 --> 09:00.767
you say in your answer that

09:00.834 --> 09:04.734
you couldn't sell the $300 gift card
for $300.

09:04.800 --> 09:08.133
You said you took a lot less for it
in order to get cash.

09:08.200 --> 09:11.033
Let me see if I remember
exactly what you said.

09:12.100 --> 09:14.600
"Even though that was not
what we agreed upon,

09:14.667 --> 09:16.600
I reluctantly accepted.

09:16.667 --> 09:21.900
I then had to sell the gift card
for half the amount it was worth

09:21.967 --> 09:23.200
so I could get cash."

09:23.266 --> 09:25.967
- That's what you wrote in your answer.
- Yep.

09:26.033 --> 09:30.233
So, not only did you accept it as payment,

09:30.300 --> 09:32.000
so that you're not owed any money anymore.

09:32.066 --> 09:36.600
I mean, you could have said to her,
"I'm not taking the $300 gift card.

09:36.667 --> 09:39.800
I'll take the $200 down payment,
but in cash,

09:39.867 --> 09:42.667
but I'm not taking the $300 gift card,"
but you accepted it.

09:42.734 --> 09:46.300
And not only did you accept it,
you disposed of it for money.

09:46.367 --> 09:48.166
You've been fully paid.

09:48.233 --> 09:51.100
Now, I would like to know, Mr. Lucas,

09:51.166 --> 09:54.233
at what point did you--

09:54.300 --> 09:55.667
according to you, 'cause you did in fact

09:55.734 --> 09:57.400
take something off the gate.

09:57.467 --> 10:00.800
- What did you take off the gate?
- Okay.

10:00.867 --> 10:02.834
After you finished working, and after...

10:02.900 --> 10:04.633
I have not been paid yet.

10:04.700 --> 10:08.066
She didn't offer to pay me with PayPal.

10:08.133 --> 10:09.500
- She told me that she had...
- Okay. But...

10:09.567 --> 10:13.867
...was expecting her unemployment.
And it hadn't come in...

10:13.934 --> 10:15.800
Just a second. Don't say anything.

10:15.867 --> 10:19.033
And it hadn't come in,
and that she couldn't pay me today.

10:19.100 --> 10:20.100
- Okay.
- Now...

10:20.166 --> 10:23.133
Oh, I got it. I want to know at what point

10:23.200 --> 10:25.667
and what exactly did you do to the gate?

10:25.734 --> 10:29.633
So after she told me that,
she, you know, I'm like,

10:29.700 --> 10:32.533
"Okay. I don't wanna deal with it.
I'm packing up my tools."

10:32.600 --> 10:34.767
And probably about 15 minutes
after that conversation,

10:34.834 --> 10:36.300
I went over and removed a--

10:36.367 --> 10:38.834
I guess it's like an ornament
that was on the gate.

10:38.900 --> 10:40.233
It was welded in four spots.

10:40.300 --> 10:41.800
It took me five minutes to do

10:41.867 --> 10:45.367
and probably fifteen minutes
to put it back on.

10:45.433 --> 10:46.734
Just a second.

10:46.800 --> 10:50.166
Tell me exactly what you did
without diminishing what you did.

10:50.233 --> 10:53.166
So, you went over to the gate, she left.

10:53.800 --> 10:56.767
You went over to the gate
because you were waiting for a locksmith

10:56.834 --> 10:59.166
because you couldn't find the keys
to your truck.

10:59.233 --> 11:03.000
You went back to the gate
and took off an ornament.

11:03.066 --> 11:04.467
- Yeah. With the assumption of...
- No, no.

11:04.533 --> 11:05.834
...and understanding that
I wasn't getting paid today.

11:05.900 --> 11:08.200
- No, no, no. It doesn't matter.
- Yeah.

11:08.266 --> 11:10.166
You took off an ornament.

11:10.233 --> 11:11.767
- Yes, I did.
- Okay.

11:11.834 --> 11:14.967
Do you have a photograph of what you did?

11:15.033 --> 11:17.200
- I think she does.
- Well, I know she does.

11:17.266 --> 11:18.734
I'm asking you if you do.

11:18.800 --> 11:20.367
- I--no, I don't.
- Okay.

11:20.433 --> 11:25.000
May I see the photographs
of what Ms. Mondin says that...

11:25.066 --> 11:26.066
Okay. This is the top.

11:26.133 --> 11:27.333
...the defendant did to the gate?

11:27.400 --> 11:28.834
This is the top where he did it.

11:28.900 --> 11:30.567
I also have on text messages...

11:30.633 --> 11:32.066
Just a second.

11:32.133 --> 11:33.467
Just a second.
Let me--can I look?

11:33.533 --> 11:36.100
- Okay.
- Just for--I'm a very simple person.

11:36.166 --> 11:37.767
I can only do one thing at a time.

11:37.834 --> 11:39.700
[Julie] Cuts, cuts.

11:39.767 --> 11:41.934
He made 16 cuts.

11:42.000 --> 11:44.567
- Eight in the front--
- Just a second, Ms. Mondin.

11:48.767 --> 11:52.400
You don't have a picture
of what was there, is that right?

11:52.467 --> 11:54.300
You mean the finished gate
before he damaged it?

11:54.367 --> 11:55.367
- Yes.
- I do not.

11:55.433 --> 11:56.433
Okay.

11:58.600 --> 12:01.700
- This is a picture of the gate.
- Yes.

12:01.767 --> 12:04.000
- As it is today?
- Yes.

12:04.066 --> 12:05.266
Okay.

12:05.734 --> 12:08.300
- Did you have it fixed?
- Not yet.

12:08.367 --> 12:10.767
Would you make circles around?

12:11.333 --> 12:13.900
So I know that you have marks here.

12:13.967 --> 12:17.667
- Right.
- Make circles around that picture

12:18.400 --> 12:20.266
to see what she's talking about.

12:20.333 --> 12:22.233
Was there a bar across?

12:22.300 --> 12:23.533
There's a frame.

12:23.600 --> 12:27.200
So, yes, there was a bar on the sides,
the top, and the bottom, and in between.

12:27.266 --> 12:29.200
Is that what he took off?

12:29.266 --> 12:31.166
- No.
- What did he take off?

12:31.233 --> 12:36.500
In order to put those decorative
flower ornaments on

12:36.567 --> 12:40.166
in under the frame so that they hang on
to the frame and they stay,

12:40.233 --> 12:44.934
you have to--as far as I know,
take a piece of iron or metal

12:45.000 --> 12:47.133
and weld that closed

12:47.200 --> 12:50.967
so that the frame is attached
to those flowery decorative parts.

12:51.033 --> 12:53.500
Is this the only gate that he worked on?

12:53.567 --> 12:55.133
Yes.

12:55.200 --> 12:59.000
And so far, you've spent over
a thousand dollars

12:59.066 --> 13:01.633
on doing one thing
or another to this gate?

13:01.700 --> 13:03.467
I paid him to build the gate.

13:03.533 --> 13:04.867
Not repair a gate.

13:04.934 --> 13:06.300
We built that gate from scratch.

13:06.367 --> 13:07.600
I designed it, he helped.

13:07.667 --> 13:08.667
I see.

13:08.734 --> 13:10.967
I also did other work
at her house as well.

13:11.033 --> 13:12.300
- So...
- Oh.

13:12.367 --> 13:13.667
Yeah. Because this looks--

13:13.734 --> 13:17.200
- Not before the gate.
- Just a second.

13:17.266 --> 13:18.266
I haven't been to your house
since after gate.

13:18.333 --> 13:19.333
Shh!

13:20.266 --> 13:22.467
If you talk to each other,
you don't need me.

13:22.533 --> 13:25.400
- Okay.
- Then I won't have a job.

13:25.467 --> 13:27.100
Then they won't have a job.

13:29.367 --> 13:33.700
So what you said to him
on December 3rd was inaccurate.

13:33.767 --> 13:36.967
You said I have had it repaired today.

13:37.033 --> 13:38.400
I anticipated that it would be done.

13:38.467 --> 13:39.567
- Just a second.
- Yeah.

13:39.633 --> 13:41.433
- That was inaccurate.
- That was inaccurate, Your Honor.

13:41.500 --> 13:42.633
Okey-dokey.

