14:06.533 --> 14:09.800
I paid him to build the gate.
Not repair a gate.

14:09.867 --> 14:12.433
We built that gate from scratch.
I designed it, he helped.

14:12.500 --> 14:13.700
I see.

14:13.767 --> 14:16.367
I also did other work
at her house as well. So...

14:16.433 --> 14:18.567
Oh. Yeah. Because this looks--

14:18.633 --> 14:21.266
- Not before the gate.
- Just a second. You may just...

14:21.333 --> 14:23.200
I haven't been to your house
since after gate.

14:23.266 --> 14:24.266
Shh!

14:25.100 --> 14:27.467
If you talk to each other,
you don't need me.

14:27.533 --> 14:29.567
- Okay.
- Then I won't have a job.

14:30.300 --> 14:31.934
Then they won't have a job.

14:33.533 --> 14:36.367
Okay. The bottom line is
you can't go and do this.

14:36.433 --> 14:38.633
You can't cut anything off at all.

14:38.700 --> 14:39.834
- No.
- You can't do anything...

14:39.900 --> 14:42.333
- No.
- Which clearly was done here.

14:42.400 --> 14:45.333
You couldn't do what you've accepted
payment, you were paid.

14:45.400 --> 14:48.500
And whether it was before or during,
if you had left in your truck,

14:48.567 --> 14:50.433
if you could find your keys,
you would have left

14:50.500 --> 14:52.500
if you didn't, you were frustrated.

14:52.567 --> 14:54.900
She left, but then in fact
you accepted payment.

14:54.967 --> 14:56.500
So that's a no-no on your part.

14:56.567 --> 14:58.400
- Correct. I understand.
- Um, that's a no-no.

14:58.467 --> 15:04.200
So do you have an estimate
to fix the gate?

15:12.734 --> 15:14.600
May I ask you a question, your Honor.

15:14.667 --> 15:17.400
- [Judge Judy] Yes.
- Is that for $200?

15:17.467 --> 15:19.333
No, it's $780.

15:19.400 --> 15:22.433
[Martin] Okay. 'Cause I have right here
a text message from her

15:22.500 --> 15:25.033
saying, "Martin, please pay me back
the sum of $200

15:25.100 --> 15:28.166
for the vandalism damage you did
to my garden gate."

15:28.233 --> 15:31.100
[Judge Judy]
May I see it? May I see that?

15:34.367 --> 15:37.734
[Martin] Originally, she asked for $250,
and then she came down to $200.

15:37.800 --> 15:39.700
- Your Honor...
- Just a second.

15:44.133 --> 15:46.500
Okay. You can take this back.

15:48.266 --> 15:51.100
November and December,
what you asked him for...

15:51.166 --> 15:52.233
[Julie grunts]

15:52.300 --> 15:54.266
...what you asked him for...

15:55.367 --> 15:59.567
was $250, half of the day's pay.

15:59.633 --> 16:01.333
- Yes.
- And he said,

16:01.400 --> 16:04.066
"I'll take care of it
a week from tomorrow."

16:04.133 --> 16:05.900
And then you wrote him again and said,

16:05.967 --> 16:09.800
"Please pay me back the sum
of $200 for the vandalism.

16:09.867 --> 16:11.900
Since you promised to come and fix it

16:11.967 --> 16:14.600
but then never showed up
or communicated back,

16:14.667 --> 16:17.667
I have had it repaired today."

16:17.734 --> 16:19.066
That's December 3rd.

16:19.133 --> 16:20.467
But that's not true,

16:20.533 --> 16:23.633
- because that estimate, that proposal...
- [Julie] Right.

16:23.700 --> 16:27.433
...that you just gave me was dated July...

16:27.500 --> 16:28.700
- Correct.
- ...29th.

16:28.767 --> 16:31.567
So you said,
"Since you promised to come and fix it,

16:31.633 --> 16:33.767
but never showed up, I had it repaired."

16:33.834 --> 16:35.367
- Well, that was in December.
- Right.

16:35.433 --> 16:38.800
So what are you giving me
a proposal for, for $780 now?

16:38.867 --> 16:42.033
Okay. The guy who was
going to repair it that day

16:42.100 --> 16:43.500
showed up and couldn't do it.

16:43.567 --> 16:44.834
And I sent the text--

16:44.900 --> 16:48.834
All right. Well then show me
the texts subsequently.

16:48.900 --> 16:50.400
- Okay. All right.
- Show me

16:50.467 --> 16:52.567
subsequently to him
where you say I have...

16:52.633 --> 16:54.867
- Yes. Okay. Here. Yeah.
- ...a new proposal? Yeah.

16:54.934 --> 16:56.767
- "I have had it repaired today."
- [Martin] Yes.

16:56.834 --> 16:58.100
- So what...
- [Julie] Right.

16:58.166 --> 16:59.767
So what you've--just a second.

16:59.834 --> 17:04.367
So what you said to him
on December 3rd was inaccurate.

17:04.433 --> 17:07.533
You said, "I have had it repaired today."

17:07.600 --> 17:09.934
- I anticipated that it would be done--
- Just a second.

17:10.000 --> 17:11.233
- Yeah.
- That was inaccurate.

17:11.300 --> 17:13.200
- [Julie] That was inaccurate, Your Honor.
- Okey-dokey.

17:20.133 --> 17:23.300
Yeah. This says, "I'll be happy to come by
and remedy any issues." He never did?

17:23.367 --> 17:26.200
He never did and he never--
he stood me up.

17:26.266 --> 17:28.333
He said, "I'll be there
a week from Saturday."

17:28.400 --> 17:31.467
I've called him.
I can prove I called him, uh, like...

17:31.533 --> 17:32.700
- Yes, you did.
- [Julie] ...um, 10 days ago.

17:32.767 --> 17:33.767
- He never answered...
- [Martin] Yes, you did.

17:33.834 --> 17:36.166
And you left me irrational messages
and it's-- I'll be honest with you...

17:36.233 --> 17:37.433
- I did leave voicemails.
- [Judge Judy] Just a second.

17:37.500 --> 17:38.700
It made me nervous to go to your house.

17:38.767 --> 17:40.433
- Oh, my go...
- Shh.

17:41.567 --> 17:45.333
Your actions today demonstrate
you can't control yourself,

17:45.400 --> 17:46.600
- is what I'm telling you.
- Okay.

17:46.667 --> 17:47.867
- That's what it--that's...
- All right.

17:47.934 --> 17:52.033
So, if you have high blood pressure,
I would take a chill pill

17:52.100 --> 17:56.867
'cause I have high blood pressure,
and, and I don't get excited, ever.

17:56.934 --> 18:00.233
Mr. Lucas, you owe her $780.

18:00.300 --> 18:01.734
That's what her proposal is

18:01.800 --> 18:04.834
to fix the damage that you did
cutting through the iron gates.

18:04.900 --> 18:07.633
You can't have a hissy fit
on somebody else's property

18:07.700 --> 18:09.834
and then accept payment for it,

18:09.900 --> 18:11.233
which you did, you got paid.

18:11.300 --> 18:12.867
So you're gonna have
to give it back to her.

18:12.934 --> 18:16.000
And she says that
she didn't have the gate fixed.

18:16.066 --> 18:19.734
She's got a proposal
from what looks like a reputable company

18:19.800 --> 18:23.367
that said that it's gonna cost
$780 to repair what you did.

18:23.433 --> 18:25.700
You can't do that.
Do you understand?

18:25.767 --> 18:27.700
Judgment for the plaintiff, $780.
We're done.

18:27.767 --> 18:29.467
- Thank you, Your Honor.
- [Kevin] Court is adjourned.

18:31.533 --> 18:34.066
Well, Judge Judy is harsh,
but she is fair.

18:34.133 --> 18:38.033
Well, I just don't think that
the judge really understood

18:38.100 --> 18:40.200
the dynamics of what happened that day.

18:40.266 --> 18:45.033
Typical kind of shyster contractor guy,
preys on single women.

18:45.100 --> 18:47.333
I showed up to go to work that day

18:47.400 --> 18:49.934
and worked an entire
eight-and-a-half-hour day.

18:50.000 --> 18:51.600
I never said I can't pay you today.

18:51.667 --> 18:53.233
I said I can't give you cash.

18:53.300 --> 18:55.900
And then when it came time
to get paid that day,

18:55.967 --> 18:57.500
she said she didn't have any money.

18:57.567 --> 18:59.533
I didn't say I didn't have money.

18:59.600 --> 19:01.100
I said I didn't have cash.

19:01.166 --> 19:04.900
I basically went over and I undid
a portion of the work that I did

19:04.967 --> 19:06.300
thinking that I wasn't getting paid.

19:06.367 --> 19:09.967
I thought that our transactions were fair
and no one was taken advantage of,

19:10.033 --> 19:12.800
but when he, like,
flipped his lid and went ballistic...

19:12.867 --> 19:15.600
$780, it was literally four welds.

19:15.667 --> 19:17.800
And so I would go with a big company--

19:17.867 --> 19:20.066
Honestly, um,
she's just a little irrational.

19:20.133 --> 19:21.467
I didn't trust her to pay me.

19:21.533 --> 19:24.400
I'm not good with, like, a single guy
who's tattooed everywhere

19:24.467 --> 19:26.033
and brings his pit bull to work.

19:26.100 --> 19:28.567
Way too high-strung.
Way too high-strung.

19:28.633 --> 19:29.800
It was the right decision.

19:29.867 --> 19:30.967
I hope I never see her again.

19:32.000 --> 19:35.266
Are there any circumstances
where somebody providing a service

19:35.333 --> 19:37.734
could forcibly remove their work,

19:37.800 --> 19:39.367
like the defendant did here

19:39.433 --> 19:42.000
if they're not paid
for what they were supposed to do?

19:42.066 --> 19:43.300
Interesting question.

19:43.367 --> 19:47.700
I don't think that
you are allowed to vandalize

19:47.767 --> 19:50.100
a property for non-payment.

19:50.166 --> 19:52.333
I think that that's what courts are for.

19:52.400 --> 19:56.333
I mean, if you take it
to the illogical degree,

19:56.400 --> 19:59.133
if you're a construction firm

19:59.200 --> 20:04.066
that provided cranes for a skyscraper,

20:04.133 --> 20:08.000
and the owner of the skyscraper
failed to pay a bill,

20:08.066 --> 20:10.600
you can't go in there
and knock down the building

20:10.667 --> 20:14.533
and say this building was made
in part because of my efforts.

20:14.600 --> 20:16.867
I understand his frustration.

20:16.934 --> 20:18.367
He was accustomed to being paid.

20:18.433 --> 20:20.800
She had always paid him,
and here he is halfway finished.

20:20.867 --> 20:25.166
He's worked an, you know,
an eight-hour day doing iron welding.

20:25.233 --> 20:28.667
And she comes out and says,
"Oh, by the way, I don't have any money"

20:28.734 --> 20:30.567
and then takes off.

20:30.633 --> 20:32.433
So I understand his frustration.

20:32.500 --> 20:34.533
But you can't vandalize
somebody's property.

20:34.600 --> 20:38.200
You have to get a new truck, go home,

20:38.266 --> 20:40.266
go to small claims court,
take out a summons,

20:40.333 --> 20:41.934
but he accepted payment.

20:42.000 --> 20:43.834
He could have rejected the payments.

20:43.900 --> 20:46.433
I'm not accepting this payment.
But he did.

20:46.500 --> 20:49.000
But during that period of hissy fit,

20:49.066 --> 20:52.200
he did vandalize her property,
and he can't do that.

